WEBVTT

00:01.302 --> 00:03.168
♪

00:03.204 --> 00:05.504
Adult mark:<i> They say</i>
<i> money can't buy happiness...</i>

00:05.573 --> 00:06.772
Mike sr: Good god!

00:06.841 --> 00:09.575
Phone bill's past due,
power bill's past due.

00:09.710 --> 00:12.511
I'm not paying my dues,
I'm paying my past dues!

00:12.513 --> 00:14.279
Adult mark:<i> But poverty</i>
<i> can't buy anything.</i>

00:14.348 --> 00:16.281
Well, you'd better
pay the tv bill.

00:16.417 --> 00:18.917
'cause I'm betting on
the tyson/frazier fight.

00:18.919 --> 00:22.321
You want me to pay a bill so
you can gamble away your money?

00:22.456 --> 00:25.791
Oh, you don't know the
first thing about investments!

00:27.528 --> 00:30.862
[dreary music]

00:30.898 --> 00:32.631
[sighs heavily]

00:33.734 --> 00:34.833
Good morning.

00:35.870 --> 00:38.270
You slept in.
You'll miss your bus.

00:38.405 --> 00:40.873
You want some toast?
Mark: No, thanks.

00:41.008 --> 00:43.008
You can eat at recess, then.

00:43.143 --> 00:45.343
Look.
I made you a special lunch.

00:45.379 --> 00:47.745
Two buns, two bags of chips,
and two pepsis, huh?

00:47.782 --> 00:50.115
Adult mark:<i> My mother</i>
<i>was killing me with kindness.</i>

00:50.184 --> 00:52.484
<i> And maybe diabetes.</i>

00:52.520 --> 00:54.286
I couldn't fit in
your sandwich.

00:54.355 --> 00:55.988
You want to eat that on the bus?

00:56.123 --> 00:58.457
That's okay.
Thanks, mom.

00:58.592 --> 01:02.294
[emotional music]

01:02.296 --> 01:05.697
♪

01:05.766 --> 01:09.200
♪

01:09.236 --> 01:12.304
♪

01:12.373 --> 01:13.772
[door slams]

01:13.774 --> 01:15.307
The redhead dumped him.

01:15.309 --> 01:17.943
Mary: What?
Pop: She's got a new boyfriend.

01:18.078 --> 01:20.512
Pop: He's a bit older.
Drives a car!

01:20.581 --> 01:22.381
I'd tell you more, but...

01:22.383 --> 01:27.252
I'm sworn to secrecy.

01:27.254 --> 01:28.187
Hey, guys.

01:28.322 --> 01:29.421
Mary: Mike, honey!

01:29.423 --> 01:30.788
Here, made you a ham sandwich.

01:30.825 --> 01:32.390
Mike jr: Oh, thank you!

01:32.460 --> 01:33.859
Mike sr: How was
the night shift?

01:33.928 --> 01:35.127
Oh, it was awesome.

01:35.262 --> 01:36.528
And you know what?

01:36.663 --> 01:37.930
I got my first cheque.

01:37.932 --> 01:39.598
Mary: Oh!
Mike sr: Oh, well done!

01:39.667 --> 01:43.268
That's my boy!

01:43.270 --> 01:44.736
That can't be right.

01:44.738 --> 01:47.539
Says here he's making 10 cents
more an hour than I am.

01:47.675 --> 01:48.806
[chuckles]
cool.

01:48.843 --> 01:49.941
Jesus murphy!

01:50.010 --> 01:51.543
You can't be making
less than your son.

01:51.678 --> 01:53.812
Well, when's the last time
you asked for a raise?

01:53.947 --> 01:55.147
Well, I...

01:55.149 --> 01:57.282
I mean, you have to...
Find the right time

01:57.284 --> 01:58.750
For this kind of...

01:58.886 --> 02:00.686
Adult mark:<i> The old man</i>
<i> hated conflict.</i>

02:00.821 --> 02:03.388
<i> He believed in living life</i>
<i> as free as a bird.</i>

02:03.390 --> 02:05.023
<i> An ostrich, specifically,</i>

02:05.159 --> 02:07.259
<i> With his head buried</i>
<i> deep in the sand.</i>

02:07.394 --> 02:10.496
Mary: The right time
is right now.

02:10.631 --> 02:13.231
Now, you get on over there
and you tell mr. Murphy

02:13.367 --> 02:15.434
That you're the heart and soul
of that station!

02:15.569 --> 02:19.704
And all that other crap
you're always telling me, hm?

02:19.773 --> 02:23.575
♪

02:23.611 --> 02:26.445
Go on.
Huss!

02:31.318 --> 02:37.055
[radio playing "every time
you go away" by paul young]

02:37.057 --> 02:39.191
Adult mark:<i> The bus</i>
<i> was where I first saw her,</i>

02:39.193 --> 02:41.793
<i> And now every inch of it</i>
<i> reminded me of her.</i>

02:41.862 --> 02:47.299
<i> ♪ you take a piece of me</i>
<i> with you...</i>
♪

02:47.434 --> 02:53.005
<i> ♪ every time you go away...</i>

02:53.007 --> 02:58.343
<i> ♪ you take a piece of me</i>
<i> with you</i>
... ♪

02:58.412 --> 03:00.946
Fox: Hey.
Mark: Hey.

03:01.015 --> 03:03.481
Adult mark:<i> Our</i>
<i> witty banter was back!</i>

03:03.517 --> 03:06.284
<i> All I had to do now</i>
<i> was not say anything stupid!</i>

03:06.353 --> 03:07.352
Mark: So...

03:07.421 --> 03:09.187
Why isn't your
boyfriend driving you?

03:09.223 --> 03:11.890
You know,
besides it being illegal.

03:11.892 --> 03:13.158
Even with a learner's permit,

03:13.293 --> 03:15.627
You should always have
an adult present in the car.

03:15.663 --> 03:17.729
Adult mark:<i> And so much</i>
<i> for that.</i>

03:17.731 --> 03:19.564
We broke up.

03:19.567 --> 03:22.568
Oh.
That's too bad.

03:22.703 --> 03:24.102
Adult mark:<i> Huzzah!</i>

03:24.171 --> 03:26.672
<i> I had defeated my enemy</i>
<i>without having to do a thing.</i>

03:26.807 --> 03:29.641
<i> I felt as powerful</i>
<i> as the noble ostrich.</i>

03:29.677 --> 03:30.909
He's a jerk.

03:31.044 --> 03:33.311
He's always trying to
get me to do gross stuff.

03:33.447 --> 03:35.513
Boys are dicks.

03:35.549 --> 03:39.651
Can I ask you
a personal question?

03:39.687 --> 03:43.188
If he's so rotten,
then why'd you even date him?

03:43.323 --> 03:45.189
In the summer,
he seemed nice

03:45.226 --> 03:47.492
Compared to everyone else
I was hanging out with,

03:47.628 --> 03:49.795
But now I realize that's 'cause

03:49.797 --> 03:53.298
The people I was
hanging out with... Suck.

03:53.433 --> 03:56.668
♪

03:56.704 --> 03:59.070
Check this out.
I got double-lunched.

03:59.106 --> 04:00.171
No way!
How?

04:00.241 --> 04:01.340
Oh, my mom.

04:01.475 --> 04:03.475
Fox: Okay, give me the chips.
Mark: Both?

04:03.544 --> 04:05.410
Adult mark:<i> The bus</i>
<i> had become a time machine,</i>

04:05.446 --> 04:06.945
<i> And by the time</i>
<i> we got to school,</i>

04:07.080 --> 04:09.281
<i> I felt as though a great</i>
<i> weight had been lifted</i>

04:09.283 --> 04:10.682
<i> From my shoulders...</i>

04:11.752 --> 04:13.151
<i>...And tied around my ankles.</i>

04:13.220 --> 04:14.486
Fox: [to mark]
that's so lame...

04:14.555 --> 04:15.821
Millard: Hey, fox!

04:15.956 --> 04:17.556
Millard: We gotta talk.
Fox: I gotta get to class.

04:17.691 --> 04:19.257
Oh, would you
just give it up?!

04:19.293 --> 04:22.027
She said she doesn't
want to talk to you.

04:23.263 --> 04:24.829
Millard: And<i> I</i> wasn't
talking to
<i> you</i>
